1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:11,537
=The Moment I Met You=

2
00:00:11,537 --> 00:00:15,000
=Episode 11=

3
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:21,920
If we're spotted,

4
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:22,960
It won't end well for us.

5
00:00:23,380 --> 00:00:24,519
Let's call a truce for now.

6
00:00:24,519 --> 00:00:25,160
Miss?

7
00:00:25,559 --> 00:00:26,719
Why should I trust you?

8
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:28,120
Miss?

9
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:30,490
The mastermind of Zuihong Parlor
is linked to multiple kidnappings.

10
00:00:30,519 --> 00:00:31,519
As the Grandmaster,

11
00:00:31,519 --> 00:00:33,400
I assume you're here
to investigate that too.

12
00:00:33,439 --> 00:00:34,399
None of your business.

13
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:36,520
Miss!

14
00:00:38,719 --> 00:00:39,359
Miss?

15
00:00:39,759 --> 00:00:40,479
Work with me,

16
00:00:41,159 --> 00:00:42,039
or these cases

17
00:00:42,039 --> 00:00:43,759
might end up being blamed on your sect.

18
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:46,000
Ms. Mei'er, I'm coming in!

19
00:00:49,159 --> 00:00:49,759
Miss?

20
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:51,560
Miss?

21
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,640
Can't you see wre're having
a moment here?

22
00:00:59,799 --> 00:01:00,679
Get lost!

23
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:05,719
Right, right.

24
00:01:05,719 --> 00:01:06,480
My apologies.

25
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:11,920
Thanks for playing along.

26
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:15,120
A thanks isn't going to be enough.

27
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,120
Come.

28
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:26,319
Sir, please, right this way.

29
00:01:28,500 --> 00:01:29,780
Ms. Mei'er will be here shortly.

30
00:01:30,159 --> 00:01:31,280
Please, have some tea.

31
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,159
Just a moment.

32
00:01:32,359 --> 00:01:34,480
So this is Ms. Mei'er's room?

33
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:35,640
Yes, this is the one.

34
00:01:36,519 --> 00:01:37,840
Fine. You may go.

35
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,599
Understood.

36
00:02:11,759 --> 00:02:12,599
This scent...

37
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,919
It's the same as Hu Mei'er's

38
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,199
and what I smelled

39
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:17,840
in Lin Xin'er's hair.

40
00:02:19,599 --> 00:02:20,475
Just as I thought.

41
00:02:20,725 --> 00:02:22,966
It's laced with Western Datura.

42
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,000
Father-in-law.

43
00:02:26,879 --> 00:02:28,759
I'm finally going to clear your name.

44
00:02:42,639 --> 00:02:43,319
You thug!

45
00:02:43,479 --> 00:02:44,759
You know I'm engaged.

46
00:02:44,759 --> 00:02:45,840
Why would you do that?

47
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,400
Because I like you, obviously.

48
00:02:49,879 --> 00:02:51,199
With a handsome guy like you,

49
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,319
it would be a waste not to steal a kiss.

50
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:57,759
What?

51
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,199
Playing the loyal husband now?

52
00:03:01,719 --> 00:03:02,639
Too late.

53
00:03:03,199 --> 00:03:04,520
If your fiancée ever found out

54
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,080
that you were kissing another woman,

55
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:07,479
what would she say?

56
00:03:07,479 --> 00:03:08,000
You...

57
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:10,400
Why? Do you want another one?

58
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,210
Haven't had enough?

59
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:12,520
Shameless!

60
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,080
Only Chang can have my heart.

61
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,039
Give it up already!

62
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,199
Wait for me.

63
00:03:24,039 --> 00:03:25,000
Wait up!

64
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:29,439
I am Mei'er, a dancer from the West.
Greetings, Squire Mei.

65
00:03:34,039 --> 00:03:36,960
The Enchantress of the West,
your reputation is well-deserved.

66
00:03:39,039 --> 00:03:39,840
I'm a songstress.

67
00:03:41,719 --> 00:03:44,639
Are you truly from the Western Regions?

68
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:48,360
You seem to have
a hint of a Southern accent.

69
00:03:50,199 --> 00:03:51,479
In my line of work,

70
00:03:51,759 --> 00:03:52,960
we travel all over.

71
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,039
Naturally, my accent has
become a bit of a blend.

72
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,159
What a coincidence.

73
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:02,479
It seems we have that in common.

74
00:04:04,639 --> 00:04:09,719
You don't strike me
as a man of the Martial World.

75
00:04:10,919 --> 00:04:14,080
And yet,
you seem very much a part of it.

76
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:19,759
Are you trying to dig into my past, sir?

77
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,319
Is there much to dig into?

78
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:24,600
Are you afraid of a little probing?

79
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Well, if you want to
get to know me better,

80
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:32,319
we should head to the inner chamber

81
00:04:34,199 --> 00:04:35,240
and take our time.

82
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,079
If I drink this,

83
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,959
will I lose my senses?

84
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:42,480
It'll just leave you head over heels.

85
00:04:46,839 --> 00:04:48,199
Then, I'll have to see for myself.

86
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:08,240
Something's wrong.

87
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:10,040
Where is everyone?

88
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,279
They must have spotted us

89
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:13,199
and cleared out.

90
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:15,199
Darn it.

91
00:05:15,730 --> 00:05:16,560
Split up and search!

92
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,959
You actually told Mao Buyu

93
00:05:20,959 --> 00:05:22,319
that I came for pleasure!

94
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:22,959
Are you itching

95
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:24,319
for a beating?

96
00:05:24,439 --> 00:05:26,079
I just wanted to see Hu Mei'er.

97
00:05:26,079 --> 00:05:26,600
You two!

98
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,959
How can you stand here chatting?

99
00:05:27,959 --> 00:05:29,519
The Zuihong Parlor gang has vanished.

100
00:05:29,519 --> 00:05:30,720
Call for backup!

101
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:31,680
Go!

102
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,680
Don't just stand there!

103
00:06:07,537 --> 00:06:10,437
(Zhuyue Nunnery)

104
00:06:19,079 --> 00:06:19,759
You're awake.

105
00:06:21,079 --> 00:06:23,279
Where is this?

106
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:25,800
We have been

107
00:06:26,319 --> 00:06:27,040
kidnapped.

108
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,759
I am Xu Anran.

109
00:06:40,639 --> 00:06:42,879
And I am Mei Guangzu.

110
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,639
Mei Guangzu?

111
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:51,759
Wait, are you Chu Yunchang's uncle?

112
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,240
And you are?

113
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,480
I'm Mao Buyu's brother-in-law.

114
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,000
What a coincidence.

115
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,480
So you frequent brothels too?

116
00:07:04,399 --> 00:07:05,920
Not at all!

117
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:07,079
I was...

118
00:07:08,279 --> 00:07:09,600
I was investigating a case.

119
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,800
A coroner investigating cases?

120
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,000
It's a long story.

121
00:07:15,759 --> 00:07:18,720
But how did you end up here, Squire Mei?

122
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:19,639
Same as you.

123
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,879
Seeking pleasure.

124
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:28,199
It looks like

125
00:07:29,439 --> 00:07:30,480
they've been captured.

126
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,410
My investigation showed

127
00:07:33,900 --> 00:07:35,399
the previous owner of Zuihong Parlor,

128
00:07:35,399 --> 00:07:37,199
Madam Du, retired three months ago.

129
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,079
This Madam Zhong

130
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:40,360
is the new owner.

131
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,079
Hu Mei'er also arrived three months ago

132
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:45,560
as a dancer from the Western Regions.

133
00:07:45,759 --> 00:07:47,680
Right after that, a string of

134
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,240
disappearances and ransoms began.

135
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:51,759
It's safe to assume

136
00:07:52,279 --> 00:07:53,920
that the crew at Zuihong Parlor

137
00:07:54,600 --> 00:07:56,279
is behind these kidnappings.

138
00:07:57,959 --> 00:07:59,519
But there isn't a single victim here.

139
00:08:00,160 --> 00:08:01,759
They must have moved them beforehand.

140
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,079
Zuihong Parlor is a public business.

141
00:08:05,519 --> 00:08:06,759
People come and go constantly.

142
00:08:07,319 --> 00:08:09,639
They wouldn't risk hiding anyone inside.

143
00:08:10,519 --> 00:08:12,399
They must be held somewhere else.

144
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:14,160
I'm worried our investigation

145
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,120
has alerted them.

146
00:08:15,759 --> 00:08:17,079
If they get desperate,

147
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,639
the hostages will be in grave danger.

148
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,079
Perhaps

149
00:08:21,519 --> 00:08:24,040
the victims are already dead.

150
00:08:24,759 --> 00:08:27,959
Perhaps those letters
were written in advance.

151
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:30,275
(Sacred Token)

152
00:08:31,279 --> 00:08:32,120
Then Anran...

153
00:08:32,450 --> 00:08:33,840
Does that mean Anran is already...

154
00:08:37,737 --> 00:08:38,377
Exactly.

155
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:42,600
For all we know,
he's already been drawn and quartered.

156
00:08:43,759 --> 00:08:45,039
How can you be so cruel?

157
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:46,990
Listen, Jade Squirrel.

158
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,500
You should just turn yourself in.

159
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:50,240
That mask of yours will

160
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,320
eventually become your face.

161
00:08:51,530 --> 00:08:52,960
By the time you want to take it off,

162
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,320
it'll tear you apart.

163
00:08:55,279 --> 00:08:57,320
Stay out of my business.

164
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,320
As if I care.

165
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,919
I hope you two had a good rest.

166
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:15,120
Miss, this is some novel
roleplay you've got going on.

167
00:09:16,062 --> 00:09:19,370
Is this an extra-charge service?

168
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,440
You think this is a game?

169
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:26,679
We have all the time
in the world to play.

170
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:27,480
How dare you!

171
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:29,440
Do you have any idea who I am?

172
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:33,879
You're from the Gate Bureau, right?

173
00:09:34,279 --> 00:09:37,200
You think that makes you special?

174
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:37,799
You...

175
00:09:45,279 --> 00:09:46,399
I already know

176
00:09:46,759 --> 00:09:48,000
who he is.

177
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:51,759
What's your story?

178
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:54,960
I'm just a wandering vagabond.

179
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:58,120
A few wealthy families in the Capital

180
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:01,440
hired me to find their missing children.

181
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:05,399
A wandering vagabond?

182
00:10:06,759 --> 00:10:08,559
I'm here for evidence of your murders.

183
00:10:10,879 --> 00:10:13,200
And who exactly did I kill?

184
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:16,519
You killed Lin Xin'er,
Lady Thousand-Hands, didn't you?

185
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,440
My nose never lies.

186
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,039
You're carrying the scent
of Western Datura.

187
00:10:21,519 --> 00:10:24,240
It's a fragrance that causes
hallucinations and madness.

188
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:26,159
If I'm not mistaken,

189
00:10:27,039 --> 00:10:29,639
you're the Nine-Tailed Fox,

190
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,200
Hu Suzhen.

191
00:10:37,919 --> 00:10:39,480
You're Lin Xin'er's senior.

192
00:10:41,399 --> 00:10:44,080
I thought I'd hidden myself well enough

193
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:45,360
here at Zuihong Parlor.

194
00:10:46,039 --> 00:10:47,639
I can't believe I slipped up.

195
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:49,919
In that case,

196
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,480
just kill them.

197
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,320
With pleasure.

198
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,279
Wait!

199
00:10:55,759 --> 00:10:58,519
We have money! Lots of it!

200
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,000
I'm rich!

201
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:01,759
And he's rich too!

202
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,919
You're only in this
for the money, right?

203
00:11:06,840 --> 00:11:08,279
You can kill us

204
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,919
after you get the ransom.

205
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,879
Move it!

206
00:11:16,879 --> 00:11:18,240
Hurry up, stop stalling!

207
00:11:26,300 --> 00:11:27,280
What are you looking at?

208
00:11:28,559 --> 00:11:29,720
Who'd want to look at you?

209
00:11:30,600 --> 00:11:31,720
It's just that

210
00:11:32,039 --> 00:11:33,919
you remind me of someone I know.

211
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,879
Moved on that quickly, have you?

212
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,759
Why not just dump your fiancée?

213
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:43,080
I might actually consider you then.

214
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:43,960
In your dreams.

215
00:11:44,279 --> 00:11:46,120
I would never leave Chang for anyone.

216
00:11:48,519 --> 00:11:49,519
You'd be a fool to do so.

217
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,559
Now take me to the morgue.

218
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:53,039
Stop wasting my time.

219
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,919
You still want to see Lin Xin'er's body?

220
00:11:56,690 --> 00:11:57,679
That's against protocol.

221
00:11:58,159 --> 00:11:58,720
Besides,

222
00:11:58,720 --> 00:12:00,399
walking into the Gate Bureau like this?

223
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:01,919
You must have a death wish.

224
00:12:02,559 --> 00:12:03,720
There are hundreds of people

225
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,159
in the Bureau and the Ministry.

226
00:12:05,639 --> 00:12:06,879
No one knows every single face.

227
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,720
And anyway, you're the one
who suggested we partner up.

228
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:11,600
Let's find

229
00:12:11,879 --> 00:12:12,759
Lin Xin'er's body.

230
00:12:12,759 --> 00:12:14,480
You clearly don't trust me.

231
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,879
That's why you're tagging along.

232
00:12:15,879 --> 00:12:17,799
You're right, I don't trust you.

233
00:12:17,799 --> 00:12:18,919
That's why I'm watching you.

234
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:30,960
Miss,

235
00:12:31,399 --> 00:12:32,559
for the first ransom,

236
00:12:32,930 --> 00:12:34,360
how does five thousand taels sound?

237
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:40,399
You certainly know the market,
don't you?

238
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:43,600
Your turn.

239
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:48,600
I am the Chief Coroner
of the Gate Bureau!

240
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:51,240
I refuse to be coerced
into writing ransom notes!

241
00:12:51,879 --> 00:12:53,600
Does death not scare you at all?

242
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:55,690
As the ancients said,

243
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:58,799
"Since time immemorial,
who has ever escaped death?"

244
00:12:59,039 --> 00:13:00,159
Shut up, you bookworm.

245
00:13:00,919 --> 00:13:02,600
You're buzzing in my ear like a fly.

246
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,559
Kill him.

247
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:04,840
Wait!

248
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:08,519
He really is just a nerd.

249
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,639
He is too rigid.

250
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,720
Allow me to talk some sense into him.

251
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,480
You have until
this incense stick burns out.

252
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,440
If it finishes burning

253
00:13:23,679 --> 00:13:25,559
and that letter isn't written,

254
00:13:25,919 --> 00:13:28,039
don't blame me for getting ruthless.

255
00:13:37,519 --> 00:13:38,480
Is it really worth it?

256
00:13:39,279 --> 00:13:41,039
Any life is better than no life at all.

257
00:13:41,039 --> 00:13:42,559
They wouldn't dare kill me.

258
00:13:42,559 --> 00:13:43,120
I am...

259
00:13:43,120 --> 00:13:44,559
I don't care who you are.

260
00:13:44,559 --> 00:13:45,960
They'll kill you regardless.

261
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,679
If you know she's the Nine-Tailed Fox,

262
00:13:48,759 --> 00:13:51,120
then you should know
the Southern Thieves

263
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:53,360
are behind all these recent kidnappings.

264
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,320
So what?

265
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,200
So far,

266
00:13:56,519 --> 00:13:58,120
has even one hostage been released

267
00:13:58,120 --> 00:13:59,210
after the ransom was paid?

268
00:14:00,879 --> 00:14:02,320
What's your point?

269
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,639
Normally, kidnappers

270
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,279
let people go once they get the money.

271
00:14:09,279 --> 00:14:10,879
But these people never let anyone go.

272
00:14:10,879 --> 00:14:13,039
They just keep demanding more.

273
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:16,279
That proves they have no intention
of leaving anyone alive.

274
00:14:16,879 --> 00:14:18,000
Once they've bled

275
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,480
the victim dry,

276
00:14:19,480 --> 00:14:21,879
they kill them to cover their tracks.

277
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:22,919
So,

278
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,519
stop throwing your title around.

279
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:28,120
To them, you're just a walking safe.

280
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:28,720
With money,

281
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:29,879
you live.

282
00:14:30,279 --> 00:14:30,960
Without money,

283
00:14:31,279 --> 00:14:32,240
you're dead meat.

284
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,000
I see.

285
00:14:35,559 --> 00:14:36,279
Understand?

286
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:38,080
So, start writing.

287
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:42,399
Fine. I'll write it.

288
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Are you done yet?

289
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,039
Too intense for you?

290
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:10,080
Just be grateful it's a cool day,
otherwise she'd be reeking.

291
00:15:10,792 --> 00:15:11,512
Stop talking

292
00:15:11,512 --> 00:15:12,512
and get it done.

293
00:15:19,759 --> 00:15:20,759
She was indeed poisoned.

294
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:22,840
It's Western Datura.

295
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:24,710
Aside from the Nine-Tailed Fox Hu Suzhen,

296
00:15:24,919 --> 00:15:25,960
hardly anyone uses it.

297
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,399
In that case,

298
00:15:29,399 --> 00:15:31,000
that dancer at Zuihong Parlor

299
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,120
isn't some Western songstress at all.

300
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,919
She's the senior
of the Southern Thieves,

301
00:15:34,919 --> 00:15:35,799
the Nine-Tailed Fox.

302
00:15:36,120 --> 00:15:36,759
Exactly.

303
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:38,700
This Nine-Tailed Fox actually

304
00:15:38,710 --> 00:15:40,799
dares to cause trouble
on Sacred Hand Sect's turf.

305
00:15:50,825 --> 00:15:54,100
♪Grudges and regrets
are like strong wine♪

306
00:15:54,138 --> 00:15:57,013
♪Drink it down and let it go♪

307
00:15:57,513 --> 00:16:03,231
♪An empty cup for our love and hate♪

308
00:16:04,413 --> 00:16:07,733
♪Tears blur a fate I can't control♪

309
00:16:07,863 --> 00:16:10,783
♪Let's drink until dawn♪

310
00:16:11,951 --> 00:16:17,191
♪Behind this mask, I'll never lie♪

311
00:16:18,413 --> 00:16:20,806
♪Every reunion feels like the first♪

312
00:16:20,806 --> 00:16:24,456
♪This hidden smile will never fade♪

313
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:28,015
♪One heart, standing by your side♪

314
00:16:28,113 --> 00:16:31,088
♪To the ends of time♪

315
00:16:31,088 --> 00:16:34,463
♪The moon traces your face♪

316
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:38,238
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

317
00:16:38,238 --> 00:16:44,478
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

318
00:16:44,813 --> 00:16:48,028
♪A silent prayer in my soul♪

319
00:16:48,313 --> 00:16:51,851
♪Carrying my vow beneath the moon♪

320
00:16:52,138 --> 00:16:55,163
♪Hoping we never drift apart again♪

321
00:16:55,163 --> 00:16:58,263
♪On our way to forever♪

322
00:16:58,263 --> 00:17:02,113
♪The moon traces your face♪

323
00:17:02,113 --> 00:17:05,473
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

324
00:17:05,663 --> 00:17:11,623
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

325
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:22,340
♪Just to be with you♪
